<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-C6AEF900-297A-4B78-8C83-0556308E73A2" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-C6AEF900-297A-4B78-8C83-0556308E73A2" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title ">5912 Matrix plate Rz out of range</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-F95B978B-749E-492D-83ED-7A914196BA08"><p class="- topic/p ">The calibration detected the matrix-plate (printhead-carriage) rotation around the Z-axis is out of range. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-B8D37B42-AC6D-41BE-A6EE-765902AA3EDB"><p class="- topic/p ">In the C16x0 there is a high change of a false positive on the error. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case one of the outer printheads is mispositioned this error is raised. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In those cases the carriage does not need to be replaces, but the printheads needs to be re-seated. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-96F37E6C-4BD0-434C-91C3-13C48794D47E" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step.</u>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is generated during the calibration steps: “ArrayRelativeLengthSandS” or “NozzleJetVar” which are part of one the following calibration sequences
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Carriage calibration
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Installation calibration via SDS 21-6-003
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> NozzleOptimalisation (M-series only)
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "><u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Patterns in calibration print.</u>
</p><table id="GUID-2CFA079D-108F-4CA3-916D-349A29E27211" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">C1640
</p><p class="- topic/p ">C1650
</p><p class="- topic/p ">C1630
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-D9606CD9-990E-4DBB-B14A-D37D32AEED07" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-9F627C08-9AA8-447C-8CE8-83B568D6CF88-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9F627C08-9AA8-447C-8CE8-83B568D6CF88-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-1D78F979-AAB3-47CE-80B5-B2A43E33A4A2" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-B16C20DE-A18D-40A9-9220-569477520D09-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B16C20DE-A18D-40A9-9220-569477520D09-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">CMxx
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-8B5DCF48-06B9-4DA2-9428-BA0EB0CC61D5" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-27697CA6-8688-435A-AE10-41BB45160436-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-27697CA6-8688-435A-AE10-41BB45160436-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-12CC039A-5613-4AA7-8F32-05D27E426533" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyse/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-D73FC0DA-CAF4-4DE6-9226-3D15C57C147F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-BE28FFBF-26F8-49D4-A83A-64852E043E8F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BE28FFBF-26F8-49D4-A83A-64852E043E8F-svg.svg"/></fig><table id="GUID-21B73BC8-842D-4971-9BBC-34A0B171567A" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">ToDo
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Decision Check whether the printheads are clean 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform manual maintenance and/or pressure-pulse wipe procedure
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">SDS 7-6-002
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Re-seat printheads (Only needed for C16x0)
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="GUID-98A2ABFB-934C-43B1-82AB-6A35CBCCFD63.xml" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: How to install (Example printhead 3)</xref>
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace printhead-carriage
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="GUID-CA044853-D7B5-442F-9553-01C6A354E232.xml" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>05 How to remove the printhead carriage unit</xref>
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-62BF0090-12B1-4370-A5B5-57DFDA17510E" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">In case the matrix-plate is rotated around the Z-axis this mainly caused by heavy mechanical forces on the printhead-carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This can happen by a severe media crash, but also during transport when the transport locking is not mounted correctly. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure that when an engine is re-located the transport locking is mounted correctly. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">(Install the transport locking material on the printer)
</p></section><section id="GUID-A49BA96B-354B-4805-B4C8-FDD54E472B21" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">All printheads are mounted into a metal matrix-plate. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This plate is part of the printhead-carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To determine the rotation around the Z-axis (Rz) of this plate a trend-line between the X-position of the printhead in relation to the Y-position is calculated.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the printhead-carriage is a bit rotated around the Z-axis (see picture below) the warning will be raised. 
</p><fig id="GUID-2D5E512C-540C-45AD-9D20-804657A05D39" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Top view Colorado printer</title><image href="GUID-11EDF1FF-6FC8-4983-AC33-65017BA80826-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-11EDF1FF-6FC8-4983-AC33-65017BA80826-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The warning is solitary based on the calculated trendline. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When one or printheads are not positioned correctly this might influence this trendline. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This will result in a false positive on the matrix-plate Rz. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In R4+ this is covered by additional warning 5936.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-480B4E14-7AB9-4230-BBE2-97A999EC3E19.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
